      "filename": "Full Stack Developer.pdf",
      "parseText": "Gowtham R.\n +91-6374133796 | gowthamdax@gmail.com | LinkedIn | GitHub\nDHAN Attendance App | DHAN Attendance and Leave Portal | Madurai, India\nProfessional Summary\nSoftware Developer with 2 years of experience building production-grade mobile and backend systems using React\njs,React Native, Node.js, and MySQL. Strong focus on system optimization and scalable architecture. Proven\nimpact in reducing operational cost, improving performance, and delivering large-scale field deployment systems.\nCurrently working at DHAN Foundation (ICT-INAYAM).\nWork Experience\nDHAN Foundation (ICT-INAYAM) Madurai, Tamil Nadu\nFull Stack Developer (2 years) Jun 2024 – Present\nKey Project: DHAN Attendance App (Google Play Store) and Dhan Attendance and Leave Portal\n– Built a React Native attendance system deployed across 16+ states, improving field reporting reliability at scale.\n– Replaced paid geolocation service (HereAPI) with Haversine Algorithm, achieving 100% cost reduction.\n– Designed a GPS-based hierarchical leave approval workflow ensuring data integrity and verification accuracy.\n– Implemented Docker-based deployments across LAN/WAN environments, improving deployment consistency.\n– Built secure SSH-based multi-developer workflow and automated deployment scripts.\n– Handled production debugging, REST API optimization, and scaling issues in live systems.\n– Built DigitalOcean Spaces cloud pipeline processing 5,000 images/day ( 1.8M/year) with optimized upload +\ncaching.\nTech Stack: React Native, Node.js, MySQL, Docker, DigitalOcean Spaces, Nginx, SSH, Git\nEducation\nB.E. Computer Science & Engineering 2020 – 2024\nSri Shakthi Institute of Engineering and Technology Coimbatore, Tamil Nadu\nTechnical Skills\nFrontend / Mobile: React Native, React.js\nBackend: Python,Node.js, Express.js, REST APIs\nDatabase: MySQL, MongoDB\nCloud / DevOps: Docker, DigitalOcean Spaces, Nginx, Git, SSH\nNotable Project\nDHAN Attendance App and Web Portal\nProduction mobile application used across 12+ Indian states. Handles GPS-based attendance and leave workflows\nwith location validation. Designed backend architecture, REST APIs, and data flow for scalable field operations.\nImplemented location distance calculation using the Haversine algorithm to replace external geolocation-based\ndependency, improving cost efficiency and system control. Implemented UUID-based device binding mechanism\nduring user registration to uniquely identify authorized devices, preventing multi-device misuse and ensuring secure\nattendance marking tied to a single registered device per employee.\nAdditional Information\nLanguages: Tamil, English, Hindi\nInterests: Scalable Systems, AI Agents, Cloud Architecture",
